<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-329-251  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 329 251.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Magazine  March 14 1989 v8 n5 p203(9)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Economic modeling. (includes related articles on economic modelinganalysis methods and the editor's choice of economic modelinganalysis software) (Software Review) (overview of six economicmodeling statistical analysis software packages.) (evaluation)andM;</TITLE><SUMMARY>The ideal econometric modeling statistical analysis softwarepackage should allow easy model creation, estimation andforecasting.andP;  Data manipulation capabilities are particularlyimportant, since the data that econometrics use is derived fromreal-world events, rather than the laboratory.andP;  Model building andsolving techniques, especially matrix algebra, are also importantelements of a good package.andP;  In addition, a wide range ofestimation techniques, and forecasting techniques that are easy touse and repeat, are also desirable.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Mikros Inc. (products)Scientific Software Inc. (products)Quantitative Micro Software (products)Odin Research (products)Alphametrics Corp. (products)Sorites Group Inc. (products).andO;Product:   ESP 2.31 (Computer program)Lisrel 7.0 (Computer program)Prelis (Computer program)Micro 6.0 (Computer program)OTIS 1.2 (Computer program)PowerStation (Utility program)Soritec 6.3 (Computer program).andO;Topic:     Software packagesStatisticsStatistical AnalysisStatistical SoftwareEvaluation.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Econometric modeling: summary of features. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>ECONOMETRIC MODELINGandM;Econometrics is the measurement of economic theory through the use ofmathematical and statistical methods.andP;  Econometric methods assist in theevaluation, comparison, and forecasting of the myriad theoretical models aneconomist may use.andP;  While statistical inference implies only the testing of awell-defined hypothesis, econometrics goes one step further by helping toformulate the model and develop a testable hypothesis.andP;  All in all,econometrics provides the bridge between data and the economic theory used tointerpret the data.andM;The ideal econometric package should allow easy model creation, estimation,and forecasting.andP;  (Dedicated forecasting packages are reviewed in the nextsection.)andP;  Data manipulation capabilities are very important, especiallysince the data economists use is derived from real-world events, not thelaboratory.andP;  Model building and solving techniques--particularly matrixalgebra--are a necessary part of a good package.andP;  A wide range of estimationtechniques is desirable to allow the widest range of model comparisonpossible.andP;  Finally, forecasting techniques should be easy to use and easy torepeat.andM;Although the products reviewed in this category all have somewhat differentmissions, one product has a strong general econometric appeal.andP;  Soritec, fromthe Sorites Group, is a very sophisticated econometric modeling andforecasting program that can solve, simulate, and forecast a broad range ofeconomic and financial models in a relatively friendly user environment.andM;Although Soritec is best suited to individuals with sophisticated researchneeds, it's also an excellent pedagogical tool.andP;  It's easy to use for basicstatistics but possesses enough versatility and sophistication to satisythose who don't want to quickly outgrow their econometric software.andO;</TEXT></DOC>